      <exercise number="x4" permid="abQ">
        <statement>
          <p permid="RkU">
            Prove that every group of order 3 is abelian.  See part (e) of the previous problem.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <hint permid="JNz">
          <p permid="Xag">
            You might as well use <m>A</m> for the identity.  This takes care of one row and one column.  There are only 4 spots left in the Cayley table.  
          </p>
